FUNSTAT(0)                      USER COMMANDS                      FUNSTAT(1)

NAME
     funstat - Go client library and command-line interface for the Funstat API

SYNOPSIS
     funstat [options] command [args...]

DESCRIPTION
     The funstat package provides both a programmatic interface (library) and
     command-line utility for accessing the Funstat API. This implementation
     follows traditional UNIX design principles with clear separation between
     library and application layers.

INSTALLATION
     Library Integration:
       go get github.com/funstat/funstat-cli/pkg/client

     Command-line Tool:
       go install github.com/funstat/funstat-cli/cmd/funstat@latest

     Build from Source:
       git clone https://github.com/funstat/funstat-cli.git
       cd funstat-cli
       make
       # or: go build -o funstat ./cmd/funstat

CONFIGURATION
     Authentication is handled via environment variable or command-line flag:

       export FUNSTAT_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"

     Alternative direct specification:
       funstat --api-key="your-api-key-here" user resolve username1

LIBRARY INTERFACE
     The client library provides a clean programmatic interface:

       #include equivalent Go import:
       import "github.com/funstat/funstat-cli/pkg/client"

     Basic Usage Pattern:
       c := client.New("api-key")                    // Constructor
       ctx := context.Background()                   // Context setup
       result, err := c.ResolveUsernames(ctx, usernames)  // API call

     Error Handling:
       All library functions return (result, error) pairs following
       standard Go conventions. Check error before using result.

     Optional Features:
       Debug mode: client.WithDebug(true)
       Custom HTTP client configuration available

COMMAND-LINE INTERFACE
     The CLI follows UNIX conventions with hierarchical subcommands:

     Global Options:
       --api-key=KEY     API authentication key
       --debug           Enable verbose debugging output

     User Operations:
       funstat user resolve USERNAME [USERNAME...]
         Resolve usernames to user IDs (Cost: 0.10 per success)

       funstat user stats USERID
         Full user statistics (Cost: 1.00)

       funstat user stats-min USERID
         Minimal user statistics (Cost: FREE)

       funstat user get-by-id USERID [USERID...]
         Retrieve user data by ID (Cost: 0.10 per success)

       funstat user groups USERID
         List user's groups (Cost: 5.00)

       funstat user groups-count USERID [--only-with-messages=BOOL]
         Count user's groups (Cost: FREE)

       funstat user messages USERID [--page=N] [--page-size=N]
                                    [--group-id=ID] [--text-contains=TEXT]
         Retrieve user messages (Cost: 10.00 per user on success)

       funstat user messages-count USERID
         Count user messages (Cost: FREE)

       funstat user names USERID
         User display name history (Cost: 3.00)

       funstat user usernames USERID
         Username history (Cost: 3.00)

     Group Operations:
       funstat group info GROUPID
         Group information (Cost: 0.01)

API COST SCHEDULE
     Operation                 Cost (Credits)
     ----------------------------------------
     User Reputation           0.00 (FREE)
     User Stats (Minimal)      0.00 (FREE)
     User Stats (Full)         1.00
     Resolve Usernames         0.10 per success
     Get Users by ID           0.10 per success
     User Groups               5.00
     User Groups Count         0.00 (FREE)
     User Messages             10.00 per user
     User Messages Count       0.00 (FREE)
     User Names History        3.00
     User Usernames History    3.00
     Group Info                0.01

DEBUGGING
     Enable debug mode for detailed request/response logging:
       funstat --debug user stats 123456789

     Library debug mode:
       client.New("key", client.WithDebug(true))

ERROR HANDLING
     The system provides structured error reporting:

     Command-line: Non-zero exit codes indicate failure
     Library: Standard Go error interface with detailed messages

     Error categories include:
       - Network connectivity issues
       - Authentication failures
       - API-specific errors
       - Input validation errors

RETURN VALUES
     Command-line tool returns 0 on success, non-zero on error.
     Library functions return (result, nil) on success, (nil, error) on failure.

ENVIRONMENT
     FUNSTAT_API_KEY    Default API authentication key

FILES
     No configuration files are used. All settings via environment or flags.

EXAMPLES
     Basic username resolution:
       funstat user resolve alice bob @charlie

     Programmatic usage:
       c := client.New(os.Getenv("FUNSTAT_API_KEY"))
       users, err := c.ResolveUsernames(ctx, []string{"alice", "bob"})
       if err != nil { /* handle error */ }

     Statistics with pagination:
       funstat user messages 123456789 --page=1 --page-size=50

DIAGNOSTICS
     All error messages are written to stderr.
     Debug output (when enabled) shows HTTP request/response details.

SEE ALSO
     go(1), curl(1)

STANDARDS
     Follows RFC 7231 (HTTP/1.1) and Go module conventions.

AUTHORS
     Funstat API client implementation.

LICENSE
